Dialogs.Dialog: We will conduct a physical fitness test next week.
Whatever, what will be will be
I see you're motivated. Look forward for the tests.
So you're going to take it easy. Are you sure you will be okay？
All right. Let the physical fitness test begin！
(Great！ I aced my physical fitness tests！)
(Huh... I didn't do that well in the physical fitness tests...)
There is going to be a quiz next week.
That's a nice mindset. Make sure you study properly.
...Don't be taking any shortcuts just because it's a quiz.
Well then, let's star with the quiz.
(Hah... I didn't do that well in the quiz...)
For the next week, you'll have to present a song as an assignment.
(Present a song for an assignment, huh...)
Nah, I don't think I need to practice

Are you really sure it's gonna be okay？
Very well, today you will present your song.
(All right！ I aced my song presentation！)
(Hah... I failed to deliver my song...)
Emm, you have until next week to submit your work.
Make sure it's a good piece for work.
Haha... I'm looking forward to it.
Now then, I will ask you to submit your work.
(All right！ My art piece was perfect！)
(Hah... My art work wasn't that great...)
Okay listen, we'll have a practice match next week.
You're really fired up, I'm counting on you.
Very well, just take it at your own pace.
Alright, let the practice matches begin！
(Hah... I didn't do that well in my match...)
Next week we will conduct a competency test.
...You have to take this seriously and study.
We will now begin the competency test.
(All right！ I aced the competency test！)
(Hah... I didn't do that well in the competency test...)
(It's my turn to write the Library Newsletter...)
(I'll give it my all！ Since it's my turn, I'll make a good newsletter！)
(Well, I think it'll be fine if I take my time...)
(Great！ I managed to do it flawlessly！)
(Hah... My newsletter wasn't popular at all...)
It's time to get ready for the next fair...
I'll do my best to prepare！

(Hah... The fair didn't go so well...)
I'm sorry to ask, but... Can we go back？
You are a life saver, I owe you one！
(This took a really long time... Can I keep doing this？)
Hey, do you have a moment？
Hey, hey. I'm sorry to bother you, but can you lend me a hand again？
Sure, what do you need help with？
Thank you！ You've saved me a lot of trouble.
(This took a really long time... Can I keep doing this？)
Ah, nice timing. Say, can I have a moment？
Of course, how can I help？

Let's see... What else needs to be done？
Thank you for helping me. Sorry for taking to much of you time.
(This took a really long time... Can I keep doing this？)
Yes, you're happened to appear in the right place. May I have a moment？
That was perfect, you saved me. Sorry for asking you out of the blue.
(This took a really long time... Can I keep doing this？)
Yo, are you alone？ Since we're both here, let's go together.
What, are you alone again？ Come on, let's go
Well then, let's take it easy for the rest of the day.
(We ended up going to school together...)
Ah-yo, you've just arrived in time.
I'm sorry for asking you, but could you open the club room when you get to school？ I was asked to do so, but I forgot something and have to go home now.
I'm sorry, but I need to ask you to open the club room again...
Oh, Otori-san. Are you working part-time？ What are you doing here？
Great！ Sorry to bother you on your day off, but I was wondering if you can help me out. The manager asked me for help, but I'm not sure if I can do it alone.
Ah, Otori-san. What's wrong...？ Were you asked for help again？
Yeah. So I'm sorry to ask you again...
Thank you, you're a huge help～.
Hey, Komari-san. Are you working part-time？ What are you doing here？
I'm in a pinch because the manager asked me to do some shopping. Hey, help me～！
Komari-san... Don't tell me, are you out shopping again？
Yes, yes. So help me out. I'm in trouble here～.
I guess I have no choice...
You got lost, huh... Okay, let's search for her together.
Huh... again. What's going on? Don't tell me that...
I have no choice. Let's look for her together.
(I'm really glad we found your mom...)
My luggage is a little heavy... *Phew*...
I see, then I'll help you carry it.
Huh, obaasan. Let me help you.
Ah, it's you from the other day.
Sorry for being a bother, thank you.

(I bought a "charm to ward off evil".)
(I brought a charm, so I think this will be okay...)
(It's fine, I should get a little closer...)
What？ Ah, I'm so sorry. Was that too loud？
I've had a sore throat lately, so I have been practicing in secret where no one is around.
Ah, can I ask what that is？

I see. Can I take a look at it？
Curious... My throat is feeling better. I wonder if it's all thanks to this charm.

Are you sure？ Thank you very much. Now I can sing again. See you！

(I don't really know if I can stay here...)

What am I doing in a place like this...
(And he's gone... Was that really Dracula's curse？)
(There's nothing around... But I can't help but being here.)
